reviews.title: Love!!
reviews.content:
This pencil is great for brows!  It took me 3-4 uses to get the hang of it (I used a black Maybelline pencil for way more years than I care to admit lol).  My natural brows are black and thin, while my natural hair color is dark brown and I often have it dyed a shade or two lighter.  My skin tone is fair to light with a neutral undertone, and quite a bit of redness. Over the years I realized the black pencil I was using just didn't look right with my hair color, but whenever I used whatever shade of brown was the next lighter shade, that looked even worse - so I just stuck with the black.   When I saw this Hourglass brow pencil online, the shade range intrigued me.  I spent a few days trying to come to terms with spending $34 on a brow pencil and finally decided to just get it.  I got it in Dark Brunette and I'm very happy with the color (I think I might even splurge another time and get it in Black since it says it wears like a "natural" black).
Anyway, I'm very happy with this product. The package looks and feels high end in the expected Hourglass style.  The actual brow color product is 1.25" long (yes I went for it and turned the wand out to the very end), so I think this pencil should last me several months - and I do my brows 5-7 days a week.  Also the spoolie brush on the end is really nice - it's soft, and does a great job softening and blending. This pencil wears really well with my very oily skin. The color stays even and in place all day yet removes easily with eye makeup remover. Thank you Hourglass for making a wearable dark brown shade!

reviews.title: My Go To!

reviews.title: expensive but lasts way longer than others

reviews.title: HG PENCIL
reviews.content: I am completely in love with this. Also in comparison to how much product you get in this vs something like browwiz makes the cost worth it, imo. Especially considering that this is legitimately the best brow product I've ever used in my life. completely natural brush like strokes. I can really shape my brows while having them look completely natural. Holy grail product for sure.

reviews.title: Slight learning curve, but you get results
reviews.content: Before purchasing this brow pencil, I'd had no luck with pencils in the past. I can barely draw on paper - rendering my overplucked eyebrows full in a natural fashion? That was a tall order, indeed! So then I tried Anastasia Beverly Hills' eyebrow pomade and brush with the spoolie, which worked wonders. However, as that product began to dry out, and the brush lost bristles, I wondered whether a pencil would be more convenient now that I had more makeup experience. Looking through Sephora's inventory I found these triangle-tip pencils, which looked like they'd have the same effect as the brow brush. I nearly chose the ABH one, since I'd used the pomade and brush, and I still use the brow gel (love it), but someone did the math and concluded that Hourglass gives you the most product for your money. I've also had wonderful luck with Hourglass as a brand: the Veil Mineral Primer is the best on the market, and my search for a foundation / concealer would have ended after the Vanish Stick if only it didn't contain talc... :-(  So anyway I chose this, and tried it as soon as I got my order. I'm still getting used to wielding a brow pencil again, and I have to really push product up so I can see it past the packaging (and retract it when I'm done), but the results are in, and my eyebrows look natural and great with about half the effort of a pomade, maybe less.

I’m forever on the hunt for the brow products I cannot live without, having pretty much secured all “categories” except where this one falls in. After trying Goof Proof and ABH Brow Definer, I decided to “splurge” on this one due to the glowing reviews and that Allure seal. Great decision on my part.

First, this is quiet honestly the most luxe brow product I own. I mean the entire packaging and the spoolie make all my other brow products look like I got them from the Dollar Tree. The application is so freaking smooth and it STAYS put. Now just putting it out there, this cannot replace my brow wiz (or benefit precisely brow) for hair like placements....but it’s perfect to define my arch more and fill in those areas that need a little “more”.

It may be a little pricey to some, but I swear once you own this one you will never look the rest the same. This is now a STAPLE in my brow game.

reviews.content: This product has changed my life. I’m sure there are better options out there where you can paint in individual hairs, but with this, I can fill in my brows quickly and effortlessly, even when I’m half asleep and not look ridiculous.

reviews.title: staple product
reviews.content: Having been using it for over 5 years now! It’s expensive yes, but so worth it. It lasts for a long time even when I use it everyday. With the pandemic, I don’t put on makeup that much anymore so I’ve been using the same brow pencil for over a year now. It has great texture and brows look very natural. I had some people ask me if I used any brow product at all because they look so naturally well kept haha I’m Asian female with black hair and I’m using Dark Brunette.

reviews.title: Absolutely love this
reviews.content: My most favorite eyebrow pencil ever. Easy to apply. Easy to touch up.

reviews.title: GOATED
reviews.content: I've been using this product for over 7 years now. I always buy one during the sale and it lasts me almost thr entire year. I can honestly say it's the best brow product I've ever used I always go back to it even though it's stupid expensive. The shape of the pencil is the perfect thickness and angle for the best brow. I mainly use it to create the outline/ define my arch  and extend the tail. Because of the built-in wax, it stands the test of humidity in the summer and doesn't smudge.

reviews.title: Excellent Brow Pencil
reviews.content: I really love how easy this brow pencil is to use and the color that it delivers. The spoolie brush feels very luxurious and soft, not like other brushes that are more firm and rough. The product blends nicely and stays in place all day without breaking up after five hours.

reviews.title: My Go To!
reviews.content: I have been using this brow pencil for years! I have tried many others but this I will ALWAYS go back to. With the arch pencil it glides so smoothly and provides excellent coverage. This is my go to as I find it matches my brows the best, as I have dark brows some dark shades just end up waaaay too dark and I don't like it. It also lasts all day / night and it lasts me for months also even if I use it everyday.

reviews.title: expensive but lasts way longer than others
reviews.content: one of the more expensive brow pencils but worth it imo. there’s more product so it lasts at least twice as long as other, more skinny pencils. I typically use a brow gel then this for definition. my holy grail!

reviews.title: HG PENCIL
reviews.content: I am completely in love with this. Also in comparison to how much product you get in this vs something like browwiz makes the cost worth it, imo. Especially considering that this is legitimately the best brow product I've ever used in my life. completely natural brush like strokes. I can really shape my brows while having them look completely natural. Holy grail product for sure.

reviews.title: Slight learning curve, but you get results
reviews.content: Before purchasing this brow pencil, I'd had no luck with pencils in the past. I can barely draw on paper - rendering my overplucked eyebrows full in a natural fashion? That was a tall order, indeed! So then I tried Anastasia Beverly Hills' eyebrow pomade and brush with the spoolie, which worked wonders. However, as that product began to dry out, and the brush lost bristles, I wondered whether a pencil would be more convenient now that I had more makeup experience. Looking through Sephora's inventory I found these triangle-tip pencils, which looked like they'd have the same effect as the brow brush. I nearly chose the ABH one, since I'd used the pomade and brush, and I still use the brow gel (love it), but someone did the math and concluded that Hourglass gives you the most product for your money. I've also had wonderful luck with Hourglass as a brand: the Veil Mineral Primer is the best on the market, and my search for a foundation / concealer would have ended after the Vanish Stick if only it didn't contain talc... :-(  So anyway I chose this, and tried it as soon as I got my order. I'm still getting used to wielding a brow pencil again, and I have to really push product up so I can see it past the packaging (and retract it when I'm done), but the results are in, and my eyebrows look natural and great with about half the effort of a pomade, maybe less.

I’m forever on the hunt for the brow products I cannot live without, having pretty much secured all “categories” except where this one falls in. After trying Goof Proof and ABH Brow Definer, I decided to “splurge” on this one due to the glowing reviews and that Allure seal. Great decision on my part.

First, this is quiet honestly the most luxe brow product I own. I mean the entire packaging and the spoolie make all my other brow products look like I got them from the Dollar Tree. The application is so freaking smooth and it STAYS put. Now just putting it out there, this cannot replace my brow wiz (or benefit precisely brow) for hair like placements....but it’s perfect to define my arch more and fill in those areas that need a little “more”.

It may be a little pricey to some, but I swear once you own this one you will never look the rest the same. This is now a STAPLE in my brow game.
